snippet.textDisplay:
Spoiler alert) I predicted love as the crazier more ruthless version of joe by episode one, one of the clues given later in the show is that hurt attracts hurt, and most people know that hurt people, hurt people.

The writers did a really good job by creating two opposite spectrums of a killer profile. For example, we almost always associate anti social "lonely boy" as one main trait but it can be the opposite, people with huge a social presense, be it online or off may also use it as a way to compensate, hide or mask their shadow self. In the last episode love says , if you looked closely " you would have seen, alluding to the fact that she was always unhinged and not really all together there, and I'm sure that's exactly what the writers were hoping the viewer would feel or sense,Similarly to when you meet someone and they tick (to many )correct boxes. The love bombing phase, she comes to his rescue when he has minor sunburn, and becomes overly concerned, impresses him by cooking him a meal before they had even had a real first date, then she leaves him romantic notes and bakes him cakes when they are “friends” it’s known as love bombing because it’s what narcs do to seduce their victims. It’s almost impossible to escape and I think the beautiful irony is that people often feel guilty for falling for psychopath narcissist but the show actually illustrates that the power of narc can take an intelligent observant person like joe and turn him into her own victim. I loved the show because it has so many layers to it when you dig deeper


Love bombing is the enchanting phase but there are red flags that people ignore because their Good traites over shadow there bad one during the early stages of entanglement, but your intuition does kick in and goes. . Mmm something's off ... but often victims turn a blind eye.

What's interesting is that love and Joe are both narcs but on very different spectrums... narcissistic behavior is on a very large spectrum it's thrown around to often,but it also involves conflicting emotions, a struggle between the inferior self and the superior self thats projected to the public. Often the image seen by the outside is different to one they fight against which is why a narc needs constant adoration, and validation, social status to allow them to believe the fake nice they created is infact their truth self, when in reality their true self is always combination of both. But they remain in conflict with this, and will do anything to not have never it exposed.

Which begs the question .. do we think love is worst than Joe... Are his murders more justified than hers? .. my answer is that the writers show you two different types of psychopath so that the audience gets to figure out who they show more empathy toward. For example, does your empathy lie with Joe? Whom was physically abused as a child, or does it lay with love who was neglected emotionally as a child...both are forms of abuse that produced two different types of crazy, My intuition, And observations says that love is darker and more disturbed because she tries so Insanely hard to pretend that she's not.. secondly Joe was willing to leave.. meaning that his self control to give her up ,something he wanted was higher than hers. Love on the other hand fears abandonment or no attention, that she was jealous of the affection her own brother gave to the au pair, and had her killed just in order for him to become co dependant on her, her need to be his martyre is greater than having empathy for the psychology trauma she caused him, she doesn't help his addiction problems, she's the result of them. Anyone who knows anything about a narcissist understands that making some one co dependant is their way of making sure you never leave them. Secondly my favorite scene is where joe say, " what the fuck" when he realized how crazy she is, it's the moment you actually realise that no two crazy people are the same, she immediately seems far more dangerous than him, she was supposed to be the better part of him not worst. People often think that guys like crazy girls.. or that good girls like bad boys, because I study psychology so passionately I can tell you there's nothing glamorous about ever inviting anyone like that into your life. My favorite character was Delilah she was the only character that made (selfless choices). The opposite of almost all the characters in the show.

Great show for psychology enthusiasts
